# Backend API Rules

- All routes return JSON. Successful responses: { data: T, success: true }
- Error responses: { error: string, success: false, code?: string }
- Every route handler wrapped in try/catch — never let unhandled errors crash the server
- Service functions (in backend/src/services/) do the actual work — routes just call them
- Environment variables accessed via process.env.VAR_NAME — never hardcoded
- Use async/await not .then()/.catch() chains
- Log errors with console.error before returning error response
- CORS configured to only allow http://localhost:5173 in development
- All Google API calls use the shared OAuth2 client from googleAuthClient.ts
- Ollama is called ONLY from ollamaService.ts — never inline in routes
